					</div>
				</div>
				<div>
					<p class="section-intro">
						
							PARA is built on open protocol infrastructure. That means public posts may be replicated
							by third-party services outside our direct control. We design the product to make
							visibility legible, not hidden.
						
					</p>
					<div class="meta-band">
						<div class="surface-card meta-card">
							<span class="meta-label">Public by default</span>
							<p>
								
									Posts, votes, and profile fields are public unless the product offers a restricted
									mode. Federation means copies may exist elsewhere.
								
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="surface-card meta-card">
							<span class="meta-label">Messages</span>
							<p>
								
									Direct and group messaging uses end-to-end encryption where the protocol supports it.
									Metadata may still be visible to infrastructure operators.
								
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="surface-card meta-card">
							<span class="meta-label">Retention</span>
							<p>
								
									We keep data as long as needed to operate the service and meet legal obligations.
									Deletion requests go to support and are handled when verifiable.
								
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
